  <h3>Dradis v2.0 (29th of January 2009)</h3>
  <p>server component:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Forget Hosts, Services and Protocols. Embrace the freedom of Nodes.</li>
    <li>Forget SOAP, embrace REST</li>
    <li>Powered by Rails 2.0 and ExtJS 2.2 (http://www.extjs.com/)</li>
    <li>Now with security! (SSL transport and user authentication)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>client component:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>adapt the wxWidgets client to the new node-note structure of the server.</li>
    <li>forget SOAP, embrace REST web services to talk to the server.</li>
    <li>refactor of the *modules* component, now *extensions*.</li>
    <li>john's string encoding extension is built-in the Dradis client.</li>
    <li>the first building blocks of the service-oriented multiverse architecture
       have been laid out.</li>
  </ul>

